Notebook[{
Cell["\<\
Goal: study the example C32 from the paper ``Thin monodromy in Sp(4) and \
Sp(6)\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] by Bajpai-Dona-Nitsche\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 
   3.986990991367077*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f1e2b4c2-47d8-4a06-a80e-\
718c90a62c97"],

Cell["\<\
This paper attempts to resolve thinness of certain subgroups of Sp(6,Z).\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 
   3.986991067125544*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ca136dbc-c323-4fa7-9673-\
cc4f2b06ac40"],

Cell["The example C-32 from Table 3 is unresolved. ", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 3.9869910269329033`*^9}, {
   3.986991068780644*^9, 
   3.986991079470739*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f3eb3eb8-cf7a-4eda-be09-\
c755859f56ed"],

Cell["\<\
In this notebook we gather evidence that it is a virtually free group.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 3.9869910269329033`*^9}, {
   3.986991068780644*^9, 
   3.986991093085511*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"86f29265-5fb4-40de-a733-\
305d7ae0e3f5"],

Cell["\<\
In particular, we draw a finite subset of its limit set, which resembles a \
cantor set nearly on a line.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 3.9869910269329033`*^9}, {
   3.986991068780644*^9, 
   3.986991131397253*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c305b38a-7bcf-4c80-af7d-\
e36da32b9674"],

Cell["This provides a reasonable guess to play ping pong.", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9869885182456703`*^9, {3.9869909722527523`*^9, 3.9869910269329033`*^9}, {
   3.986991068780644*^9, 3.986991145028442*^9}, {3.9869944721703167`*^9, 
   3.986994472170763*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b6adcfbd-d7ce-42d4-b819-\
8ff0e18ff228"],

Cell["Readers may skip ahead to the pictures.", "Item",
