  3.989671829738901*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"57d66304-5822-4725-bdfc-\
a7d136eb5c44"],

Cell["I want to plot the cone {Hy >0 } in mathematica", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.989307952024477*^9, 3.989307953276813*^9}, {
  3.9893084161358232`*^9, 3.9893084161368713`*^9}, {3.989308581831064*^9, 
  3.989308630687955*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"40c12dcf-f295-4ae0-9332-\
5edab468198a"],

Cell["\<\
what i can do is find the extremal rays in R^6, consider these as points in \
an affine chart in RP^5, project these to R^3, and take the convex hull.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.989307952024477*^9, 3.989307953276813*^9}, {
  3.9893084161358232`*^9, 3.9893084161368713`*^9}, {3.989308581831064*^9, 
  3.989308694231656*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b38af3bd-3762-4dcd-a54e-\
5a296a5ff8b5"],

Cell["\<\
in fact, thanks to the dominance chambers, this lives inside a box in R^5 \
(then in R^3 as well).\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.989307952024477*^9, 3.989307953276813*^9}, {
  3.9893084161358232`*^9, 3.9893084161368713`*^9}, {3.989308581831064*^9, 
  3.989308717183433*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5b332f73-2848-40cc-aeb6-\
33352e0905f9"],

Cell["\<\
should also draw the transformed limit set under this conjugation, using all \
the points from steve. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.989307952024477*^9, 3.989307953276813*^9}, {
  3.9893084161358232`*^9, 3.9893084161368713`*^9}, {3.989308581831064*^9, 
  3.9893087369722757`*^9}, {3.989671691176908*^9, 
  3.9896716911778307`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"43c3398b-65e8-4ddb-826a-\
9244c2ffd8a9"],

